snippet.textDisplay:
My first-ever Sculpey project was a Sonic the Hedgehog inspired raccoon lady she turned out really cool she didn't have a skeleton though so she cracked well that's kind of a lie I put toothpicks in her legs but it was a school project so I was supposed to figure it out by myself kind of ... she turned out really good other than the leg crack and then somebody dropped her and her leg broke off😱 so I had to glue it back on I also used toothpicks in the hands for her claws I should find her and display her somewhere on a Shelf oh and the way I got her to stand upright was her big fluffy tail and acts like a kickstand LOL my second Sculpey was a rose with a wire skeleton going through the stem and then I also made a wire decoration thingy to surround it so it looked like something cool ... that also broke because the wire surrounding cool thing fell off and then the top of the Rose head broke off the teeny tiny little flower stem neck but it was really cool because I made the flower zebra stripes!!!! basically what I'm saying is Sculpey is awesome and I wish I had some right now instead I'm sitting on my couch watching my child play with toys(ADORABLE) waiting for a DVD shelf to be delivered so I can build it lol...


... I also made a really cool cobra um... R.I.P Cobra Sculpey LOL... they were in storage and they broke Okay😫 lol but it's fine I could always make new things the only thing I'm mad about is I put about a hundred billion layers of gloss paint on it to make it glossy and now was for nothing!😣 Lol
